ted women who have made a special mark in the History of India and the world. Whether it’s business, technology, politics, or any other field, women have stood strong and proven themselves in leadership roles ranging from CEO to Prime Minister.<br><br>Let’s take a route through all these celebrated women in India who have won fame across the map and how they celebrate their style as a saree. <br><br><b><i>Are you ready to meet those “naari in a saree?”</i></b></span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-2-1678214608014.png?v=1678214612" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-2-1678214608014.png?v=1678214612 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-2-1678214608014_500x.png?v=1678214612 320w" width="1200" height="628" style="aspect-ratio:1200 / 628" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-18_"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-19_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-21_"><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soumya_Swaminathan" target="_blank"></a><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Soumya_Swaminathan" target="_blank"></a><i><b><span style="color: rgb(0, 71, 178);"><br>Dr. Soumya Swaminathan – Chief Scientist of WHO</span></b></i></span></h3><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-22_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-24_">The Indian pediatrician and clinical scientist is serving as the chief scientist of the World Health Organization since March 2019. She previously chaired the WHO, ICMR, and the AIIMS New Delhi. She is highly known for her globally-recognized research on HIV and tuberculosis and her work as a member of the high scientific panel at the Global Health Summit. <br><br>The distinguished Indian scientist has been honored with several awards, including fellowships from eminent Indian science academies and a lifetime achievement award from the Indian Association of Applied Microbiologists.<br><br>Here is a glam and sho-sha style of Dr. Soumya in a saree. She prefers simple cotton, and tussar and often we have seen her choosing embroidery sarees or batik work, or raw silks in her daily wardrobe when she attends various health summits in and out of India. </span></p><img src="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-1678214879303.png?v=1678214885" srcSet="https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-1678214879303.png?v=1678214885 1536w, https://cdn.shopify.com/s/files/1/1469/7362/t/54/assets/pastel-pink-minimalist-business-blogger-facebook-ad-1678214879303_500x.png?v=1678214885 320w" width="1200" height="628" style="aspect-ratio:1200 / 628" data-pf-type="Image3" class="sc-nVkyK eXnudJ pf-81_"/><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-26_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-28_"><br><i style=""></i></span></h3><h3 data-pf-type="Heading" class="sc-cTAqQK eHolsa pf-29_"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-31_"><span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><i><b><a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Madhabi_Puri_Buch" target="_blank">Madhabi Puri Buch - Chairperson of SEBI</a></b></i></span></span></h3><p class="sc-jtXEFf jydWoQ pf-32_" data-pf-type="Paragraph"><span data-pf-type="Text" class="sc-jKTccl dCeBIC pf-34_">Last March 2022, she was appointed as the new chairperson of the Securities &amp; Exchange Board of India <span style="color: rgb(0, 102, 204);"><i><b>(<a href="https://www.sebi.gov.in/" target="_blank">SEBI</a>),</b></i></span> thus making her the first woman to head SEBI as well as the first former private sector top-level executive to lead the markets regulator. An alumna of St. Stephens Delhi and IIM Ahmedabad, the experie